		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in curl. When libcurl is built to use wolfSSL as the TLS backend, it skips certificate verification for a QUIC connection if an unknown/bad cipher or curve is used. \n            STATEMENT: The curl packages as shipped by Red Hat Enterprise Linux and RHSCL are not affected by this vulnerability because it does not have support for wolfSSL.",
